Preconditions:
The input matrix `grid` must not be null.
The input matrix `grid` must have at least one row and one column.
The input matrix `grid` must be a square matrix, i.e., the number of rows must be equal to the number of columns.
The elements in the input matrix `grid` must be integers.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer representing the minimum sum of a falling path with non-zero shifts.
The input matrix `grid` should remain unchanged after the method is executed.